cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.PF

This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspects of P2P content distribution, specifically the impact of locality on inter-ISP traffic and download completion time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also touches upon issues related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and system performance (cs.SI), as well as security and privacy (cs.CR) and parallel computing (cs.PF). However, these topics are not the main focus of the paper and are only briefly mentioned.
